snippet.textDisplay: Everyone's saying that she made a mistake by chosing Peter because their relationship was so difficult, but isn't that actually the whole point? She chose him because she loves him and because she's willing to work on their relationship, whereas with John Ambrose, it's just a dreamy kind of "what could have been" but she doesn't have those feelings for him anymore. Of course it sucks for John Ambrose but that's life I guess. It doesn't matter who is "easier to be around" or who did or didn't like who in the past, it's about who she WANTS to be with.

snippet.textDisplay: To give a little bit of credit to this movie I’d like to mention that aside from the cringy moments, some situations were a bit realistic or relatable. The part where Lara is confused on who she should be with, even though it’s pretty clear who she has a real connection with. And  it leads to the her picking the guy who doesn’t really make an effort in the relationship (we’ve all been there where you feel it in your gut that you’re gonna end up getting hurt in the end but pick the jerk anyway). And through the POV of John Ambrose, some of us can relate to being led on and then being left without any explanation. You’re left with so many thoughts wondering why you weren’t good enough, or what went wrong,  Bro I fucking felt that! 😔🤙🏻

And  it leads to the her picking the guy who doesn’t really make an effort in the relationship (we’ve all been there where you feel it in your gut that you’re gonna end up getting hurt in the end but pick the jerk anyway). And through the POV of John Ambrose, some of us can relate to being led on and then being left without any explanation. You’re left with so many thoughts wondering why you weren’t good enough, or what went wrong,  Bro I fucking felt that! 😔🤙🏻
